      "uuid": "6add7f13-b11d-41fc-aae8-e09e41b20431",
      "text": " Based on the images provided, I can create a wireframe representing the structure of this website. Here's a textual description of how I would wireframe it:\n\n\n\n```\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 800 600\">\n  <!-- Header -->\n  <rect x=\"0\" y=\"0\" width=\"800\" height=\"60\" fill=\"#e0e0e0\"/>\n  <text x=\"20\" y=\"35\" font-family=\"Arial\" font-size=\"20\">Logo</text>\n  <text x=\"700\" y=\"35\" font-family=\"Arial\" font-size=\"20\">Menu</text>\n  \n  <!-- Main content area -->\n  <rect x=\"0\" y=\"60\" width=\"800\" height=\"400\" fill=\"#f0f0f0\"/>\n  \n  <!-- Large image/banner -->\n  <rect x=\"20\" y=\"80\" width=\"760\" height=\"200\" fill=\"#d0d0d0\"/>\n  <text x=\"370\" y=\"180\" font-family=\"Arial\" font-size=\"20\" text-anchor=\"middle\">Large Image/Banner</text>\n  \n  <!-- Capabilities section -->\n  <text x=\"20\" y=\"310\" font-family=\"Arial\" font-size=\"18\" font-weight=\"bold\">Capabilities</text>\n  <rect x=\"20\" y=\"320\" width=\"240\" height=\"120\" fill=\"#d0d0d0\"/>\n  <rect x=\"280\" y=\"320\" width=\"240\" height=\"120\" fill=\"#d0d0d0\"/>\n  <rect x=\"540\" y=\"320\" width=\"240\" height=\"120\" fill=\"#d0d0d0\"/>\n  \n  <!-- \"We Are\" section -->\n  <circle cx=\"400\" cy=\"500\" r=\"30\" fill=\"#d0d0d0\"/>\n  <text x=\"450\" y=\"490\" font-family=\"Arial\" font-size=\"18\" font-weight=\"bold\">We Are:</text>\n  <rect x=\"450\" y=\"500\" width=\"300\" height=\"60\" fill=\"#e0e0e0\"/>\n  \n  <!-- Footer -->\n  <rect x=\"0\" y=\"580\" width=\"800\" height=\"20\" fill=\"#e0e0e0\"/>\n  <text x=\"20\" y=\"595\" font-family=\"Arial\" font-size=\"12\">Footer content</text>\n</svg>\n```\n\nThis wireframe represents the structure of the website based on the images provided:\n\n1. Header: Contains a logo on the left and menu on the right.\n2. Main content area:\n   a. Large image or banner at the top\n   b. \"Capabilities\" section with three columns of images/content\n   c. \"We Are\" section with a circular logo and text description\n3. Footer at the bottom\n\nThe layout is clean and modern, emphasizing visual content with supporting text. The \"Capabilities\" section showcases different aspects of the company's work, while the \"We Are\" section provides a brief company description or mission statement.\n\nWould you like me to explain any part of this wireframe in more detail or make any modifications?",
